Sentencas: The effect of strontium content on Cr deposition and poisoning in barium strontium cobalt ferrite electrodes, Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSCF, 0.3 <= x <= 0.7), was investigated at 900 degrees C for 20 h with a cathodic polarization of 200 mA cm(-2).
Titulo: Effect of Strontium Content on Chromium Deposition and Poisoning in Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-δ (0.3 ≤ x ≤ 0.7) Cathodes of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In contrast to the superb and stable electrochemical performance of the BSCF electrodes without interconnects, electrode polarization resistance and overpotential (R-E and eta) were found to increase for the O-2 reduction reaction on BSCF electrodes in the presence of Fe-Cr metallic interconnects.
Titulo: Effect of Strontium Content on Chromium Deposition and Poisoning in Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-δ (0.3 ≤ x ≤ 0.7) Cathodes of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Most important, the increase in R-E and eta values, Delta R-E and Delta eta measured after polarized at 200 mA cm(-2) for 20 h, increased significantly as the Sr content of the BSCF electrodes was increased, indicating that the Sr content in BSCF electrodes is a governing factor in Cr poisoning.
Titulo: Effect of Strontium Content on Chromium Deposition and Poisoning in Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-δ (0.3 ≤ x ≤ 0.7) Cathodes of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) analysis of the BSCF electrodes after the Cr poisoning test at 900 degrees C for 20 h revealed the presence of Cr deposits on the cathode surface.
Titulo: Effect of Strontium Content on Chromium Deposition and Poisoning in Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-δ (0.3 ≤ x ≤ 0.7) Cathodes of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The magnitude of Cr deposits on the electrode surface under the rib of the interconnect is significantly higher than that under the channel of the interconnect.
Titulo: Effect of Strontium Content on Chromium Deposition and Poisoning in Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-δ (0.3 ≤ x ≤ 0.7) Cathodes of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The results in this study indicate that Sr and/or Ba segregation plays an important role in the Cr deposition and poisoning for the O-2 reduction on BSCF cathodes, which is closely related to the Ba/Sr ratio of the cathode.
Titulo: Effect of Strontium Content on Chromium Deposition and Poisoning in Ba1-xSrxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-δ (0.3 ≤ x ≤ 0.7) Cathodes of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
